              "response": "Shared Context Collections are reusable collections of coding standards, best practices, and guidelines that are automatically available to all team projects. They allow teams to create a consistent set of rules and recommendations that can be inherited by all projects within the team.\n\nThe workflow for using Shared Context Collections involves several steps:\n\n1. A Team Admin creates a Shared Context Collection.\n2. Coding standards are uploaded to the collection using the `rlm_upload_shared_document` function.\n3. All team projects automatically inherit the standards from the collection.\n4. Team members can query the shared context using `rlm_shared_context()` to retrieve team rules.\n5. Implementation of code follows these team conventions automatically.\n\nThe collections are categorized by priority, including MANDATORY rules (highest priority), BEST_PRACTICES, GUIDELINES, and REFERENCE, which helps in managing the importance of each document within the collection (Section: Team Best Practices with Shared Context Collections).",
