              "response": "When a user exceeds their monthly query limit, the API returns a **429 Too Many Requests** response with the following details:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": false,\n  \"error\": \"Monthly query limit exceeded\",\n  \"usage\": {\n    \"current\": 101,\n    \"max\": 100,\n    \"exceeded\": true,\n    \"reset_at\": \"2026-02-01T00:00:00Z\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThe response includes:\n- `current`: Current usage count this billing period\n- `max`: Maximum allowed queries (-1 for unlimited)\n- `exceeded`: Whether the limit has been reached\n- `reset_at`: ISO 8601 timestamp when the limit resets (monthly) \n\nThis information is found in the \"What Happens When Limits Are Exceeded\" section.",
